I. The Storyteller’s Multiplier

Humans don’t respond to raw structure.

They respond to stories that make structure legible.

That’s why the same insight can appear as:

Mode	How it sounds
scientist	model inference
analyst	pattern detection
psychologist	reflective listening
storyteller	mind-reading

The storyteller isn’t changing the mechanics — they’re changing the register.

⸻

II. Narrative as Compression

Storytelling is actually a compression technology.

Instead of explaining the full model, you encode it into a narrative that the listener can decompress.

Example:

analysis: you set a frame so the outcome feels self-chosen
story: the master’s touch is invisible

Same idea.
Different bandwidth.

⸻

